			This entry was posted<span class="by-author"> by <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://elidourado.com/blog/author/elidourado/" title="View all posts by Eli Dourado" rel="author">Eli Dourado</a></span></span> on <a href="http://elidourado.com/blog/forensic-semantics-liquidity-trap/" title="1:16 pm" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2011-03-19T13:16:05+00:00">March 19, 2011</time></a>.<br /><a href="http://elidourado.com/blog/tag/" style="text-decoration:none"><i class="fa fa-tags"></i></a> <a href="http://elidourado.com/blog/tag/cowen/" rel="tag">Cowen</a>, <a href="http://elidourado.com/blog/tag/fiscal-policy/" rel="tag">fiscal policy</a>, <a href="http://elidourado.com/blog/tag/keynes/" rel="tag">Keynes</a>, <a href="http://elidourado.com/blog/tag/keynesianism/" rel="tag">Keynesianism</a>, <a href="http://elidourado.com/blog/tag/kling/" rel="tag">Kling</a>, <a href="http://elidourado.com/blog/tag/krugman/" rel="tag">Krugman</a>, <a href="http://elidourado.com/blog/tag/liquidity-trap/" rel="tag">liquidity trap</a>, <a href="http://elidourado.com/blog/tag/monetary-policy/" rel="tag">monetary policy</a><br /><i class="fa fa-btc"></i> Tip via Bitcoin at <a href="bitcoin:1FMxbQLh2hEoWXgM4GggbSAMoR61iL7zdp"> 1FMxbQLh2hEoWXgM4GggbSAMoR61iL7zdp </a>											</footer><!-- .entry-meta -->
